def data_research(dataset):
    
    display(dataset.head())
    display(dataset.tail())
    print()
    
    print('-----   -----\n')
    print(dataset.info())
    
    print('\n\n-----  -----\n')
    print(dataset.isna().sum())
    
    print('\n\n-----  -----\n')
    print(f'  : '\
          f'{round((dataset.isna().sum().sum() / (dataset.shape[0] * dataset.shape[1]) * 100), 1)}%\n')
    print('  :')
    display(pd.DataFrame(dataset.isna().mean()*100).style.set_precision(1).background_gradient('coolwarm'))
    
    print('\n\n----- -----')
    display(dataset.describe())
    
    print('\n\n-----     -----\n')
    axes = dataset.hist(figsize=(10, 10))

        #   
    for ax in axes.flatten():
        ax.set_xlabel(ax.get_title(), fontsize=12)
        ax.set_ylabel(' ', fontsize=12)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def empty_cells(column):
    print('    :', 
          data.loc[data[column].isna()].shape[0])
    
    print(f'    :', \
          f'{round(data.loc[data[column].isna()].shape[0] / data.shape[0] * 100, 2)}%')
    
    display(data.loc[data[column].isna()].head())
In [4]:
#         
def games_sales_pivot(data, region, column):
    result = data.pivot_table(index=column, 
                              values=region, 
                              aggfunc='sum')\
                 .sort_values(by=region, 
                              ascending=False)
    return result

def regions_pie_plots(column, name):
    #    ,   
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6))
    fig.suptitle(f'  {name}  ')

    #    c        `games_sales_pivot`
    for i, region in enumerate(actual_data.columns[4:7]):
        region_sales = games_sales_pivot(actual_data, region, column)
    
        #  -5      'others'
        top = region_sales.head(5).copy()
        if column != 'rating':
            top.loc['Others'] = region_sales.tail(len(region_sales) - 5)[region].sum()
    
        #      
        axs[i].pie(top[region].values, labels=top.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
        axs[i].set_title([' ', '', ''][i])
    
    plt.show()

info_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year_of_release', 'amount', 'share'])

for year in sorted(data['year_of_release'].unique()):
    empty = ((data['critic_score'].isna()) & (data['user_score'].isna()) & (data['rating'] == 'Not rated'))
    amount = data.loc[(data['year_of_release'] == year) & empty].shape[0]
    share = amount / data.loc[data['year_of_release'] == year].shape[0]
    info_df = info_df.append({'year_of_release': year, 
                              'amount': amount, 
                              'share': round(share * 100, 2)}, 
                             ignore_index=True)

#   DataFrame   
results = pd.DataFrame(columns=['platform', 'released', 'lifespan', 'years_to_peak'])

#   
for platform in games_sales_pivot(data, 'total_sales', 'platform').index[:6]:
    platform_data = data[data['platform'] == platform]
    
    #    
    released = platform_data['year_of_release'].min()
    
    #    
    lifespan = platform_data['year_of_release'].max() - released
    
    # ,           
    peak_year = platform_data.groupby('year_of_release')['total_sales'].sum().idxmax()
    years_to_peak = peak_year - platform_data['year_of_release'].min()
    
    #    DataFrame
    results = results.append({'platform': platform, 'released': released, 'lifespan': lifespan, 'years_to_peak': years_to_peak}, ignore_index=True)
